{
  "name": "Excellent Chakra Spears",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Non%20Elemental.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You create eight spears of highly condensed chakra that you then launch simultaneously. All creatures in a 60-foot cone originating from you, must make a Dexterity Saving throw, taking 10d6 damage on a failed save or half as much on a successful one.</p><p>If you have a nature release, this jutsu gains a single nature release keyword that you can cast and it's damage type becomes the corresponding nature releases damage type (Water = Cold). If you do not have a nature release this jutsu instead deals Force Damage. All effects imparted by the different nature releases can only be removed by a Jutsu</p><p>• Force: The damage die increases to a d10.</p><p>• Earth: On a failed save, a creature gains 2 ranks of Bruised.</p><p>• Wind: On a failed save, a creature gains 2 rank of Lacerated.</p><p>• Fire: On a failed save, a creature gains 2 ranks of Burned.</p><p>• Water: On a failed save, a creature gains 2 ranks of chilled.</p><p>• Lightning: On a failed save, a creature gains 2 ranks of shocked.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
